    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-21T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-21T22:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50/11–2244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-22T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >November 22, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1884. As indicated in press reports, there has been put in progress the
                    organization of a Chinese War Production Board headed by Wong Wen-hao, Minister
                    of Economic Affairs, with the following departments and heads thereof: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Priorities: Peng Hsueh-pei, concurrently Vice-Director of WPB and
                            Deputy Secretary General of Central Planning Board.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Stores: Chang Tsu-kai, concurrently Associate Director Industrial and
                            Mining Adjustment Administration, Ministry of Economic Affairs.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Manufacture: Pao Ko-yung, concurrently Director of Industrial
                            Division, National Resources Commission, Ministry of Economic
                            Affairs.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>Ordnance: Yang Chi-tseng, concurrently Director of Department of
                            Ordnance, Ministry of War.</item>
                        <label>(5)</label>
                        <item>Purchasing: Yen Chia-chin, former Commissioner of Reconstruction of
                            Fukien Province.</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>Secretariat: Wu Chin-chao, Ministry of Economic Affairs official, now
                            in the United States, who has been instructed to return to China.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Nomination of heads of transportation and finance departments and chief
                    accountant still under consideration. A directive governing the organization and
                    operation of the new board is expected to be issued shortly and further details
                    will be reported in due course.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
